about.description:
ProxyChains is a UNIX program, that hooks network-related libc functions
in DYNAMICALLY LINKED programs via a preloaded DLL (dlsym(), LD_PRELOAD)
and redirects the connections through SOCKS4a/5 or HTTP proxies.
It supports TCP only (no UDP/ICMP etc).
about.summary: a preloader which hooks calls to sockets in dynamically linked programs and redirects it through one or more socks/http proxies

name: proxychains-ng
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "proxychains-ng" %}
{% set version = "4.17" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/rofl0r/proxychains-ng/releases/download/v{{ version }}/proxychains-ng-{{ version }}.tar.xz
  sha256: 36ddc7f64cb3df2ca4170627c6e0f0dea33d1a6d0730629dff6f5c633f2006f9

build:
  skip: true  # [win or osx]
  number: 0
  run_exports:
    - {{ pin_subpackage('proxychains-ng') }}

requirements:
  build:
    - make
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ stdlib('c') }}

test:
  commands:
    - proxychains4 --help | grep Usage

about:
  home: https://github.com/rofl0r/proxychains-ng
  summary: 'a preloader which hooks calls to sockets in dynamically linked programs and redirects it through one or more socks/http proxies'
  description: |
    ProxyChains is a UNIX program, that hooks network-related libc functions
    in DYNAMICALLY LINKED programs via a preloaded DLL (dlsym(), LD_PRELOAD)
    and redirects the connections through SOCKS4a/5 or HTTP proxies.
    It supports TCP only (no UDP/ICMP etc).
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: COPYING

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - PragmaTwice
